.PP
\[en] title: TRACEE\-LIST\-DEPS section: 1 header: Tracee List Deps
Command Manual date: 2026/07 \&...
.SS NAME
tracee \f[B]list deps\f[R] \- Show an event\[cq]s dependency graph
.SS SYNOPSIS
tracee \f[B]list deps\f[R] <event> [event\&...]
[\-\-format FORMAT]
.SS DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]list deps\f[R] command shows the dependency graph of one or
more events: the base events each one needs, annotated with probe and
kernel\-symbol dependencies.
.PP
Detector and derived events expand into the base events they consume, so
this also reveals which raw events a detector chain ultimately rests on.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-\-format\f[R], \f[B]\-f\f[R] FORMAT
Output format.
One of:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]tree\f[R]
(default) an ASCII indented tree.
.TP
\f[B]mermaid\f[R]
a fenced mermaid flowchart, ready to paste into documentation.
.TP
\f[B]json\f[R]
structured output for scripting.
.RE
.SS EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Show the dependencies of a network event:
.IP
.EX
tracee list deps net_packet_icmp
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
Render a mermaid diagram:
.IP
.EX
tracee list deps sched_process_exec \-\-format mermaid
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
Emit JSON for scripting:
.IP
.EX
tracee list deps security_file_open \-\-format json
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
Inspect several events at once:
.IP
.EX
tracee list deps net_packet_icmp security_file_open
.EE
